{"id":"project-LICHEN-aez4","title":"senml_encode_battery percent parameter not bounds-checked","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/senml/senml.c
Lines: 341-370, specifically line 354

CATEGORY: CORRECTNESS

senml_encode_battery() accepts uint8_t percent (0-255) but battery percentage semantically should be 0-100:

  ret = senml_add_float(&pack, 'pct', '%', (float)percent);

Values 101-255 are encoded without error but are semantically invalid.

IMPACT:
- Invalid data (e.g., 150% battery) propagates to receivers
- Could indicate sensor malfunction or overflow not caught at source
- Violates expected semantics of percentage

FIX: Add validation:
  if (percent > 100) {
      return -ERANGE;
  }

Or document that values > 100 are valid (some systems report > 100% during calibration).","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:53:14.578165Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:53:14.578199Z"}

